cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with image set matching and uses deep neural networks for representation learning and hashing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning-based hashing, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of set-specific and database-wide distribution information suggests the involvement of information retrieval techniques, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also deals with image retrieval, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of deep neural networks for representation learning and hashing suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
